reviewText:
While new generation simracing softwares are promising, this the one !
Not for the usual gamer though. Requires a lot of skill and practice. You can only taste it fully with a good wheel-and-pedals set.
- Great physics, focused on realism;
- Awsome engine sounds;
- Graphics good enough, with attention to cars/tracks models details and fidelity;
- Big variety, from rental karts to lots of different F-One eras.
- The best wheel force feedback of them all.
- The best you can get from Artificial-Inteligence Opponents.
- Even better through leagues online. You may stumble on most of the real Brazilian Stock Car real drivers (if you can be fast enough not to eat their dust).

A must for every simracer out there.
